.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-ROUTES 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.11.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-routes \- provider-specific static routes for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I routes
file defines static routes to be added to provider routing tables defined in
.IR shorewall\-nft\-providers (5).
Routes are installed in the named provider table at firewall start.
.PP
The
.B live-apply path
is
.BR runtime.apply.apply_iproute2_rules() ,
which uses pyroute2
.B IPRoute
directly (zero shell-outs).  The operator-facing generator
.B shorewall\-nft generate\-iproute2\-rules
emits the equivalent shell script for human review or offline use.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/routes
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
PROVIDER	yes	Provider name (from providers file) or table number
DEST	yes	Destination network (CIDR) or default
GATEWAY	no	Next-hop gateway (or - for directly connected)
DEVICE	no	Interface to use for this route
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Default route in provider table:
.RS
.nf
#PROVIDER  DEST     GATEWAY
isp1       default  203.0.113.1
isp2       default  198.51.100.1
.fi
.RE
.PP
Specific route for management traffic via ISP1:
.RS
.nf
isp1       10.0.99.0/24   203.0.113.1
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-providers (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rtrules (5)

